# Sticky Frontend — Project Context

This is the Sticky spaced-repetition frontend app. The following documentation files are the single source of truth for all development work and MUST be read and followed for every task:

## Required Context Documents

1. **`docs/FRONTEND_API_SPEC.md`** — Complete API specification, GraphQL operations, auth flow, screen map, development workflow, and build chunks. This is the primary reference for all frontend work.
2. **`docs/FSRS_REFERENCE.md`** — FSRS algorithm reference (state machine, ratings, ts-fsrs types). Needed for understanding review scheduling.
3. **`docs/API_ACTION_CATALOG.md`** — Maps every user action to its GraphQL operation and delivery phase (V1 vs V1.1+).
4. **`docs/DECISION_LOG.md`** — Settled technical decisions. Never re-debate what's already decided here.
5. **`docs/ERROR_JOURNAL.md`** — Known bugs and fixes. Check before debugging to avoid re-encountering solved issues.

## Rules

- Always read the relevant docs before making changes.
- Follow the modular development lifecycle defined in the API spec (Section 18).
- Keep the Decision Log and Error Journal updated after each session.
- The backend GraphQL API runs at `http://localhost:4000` — never mock it during development.
- Build in chunks, test each chunk before moving on.
